        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 18 at 3:14PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 314 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm over
Rose, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Colcord...                        Leach...
Twin Oaks...                      Rose...
Kansas...                         Lake Eucha State Park...
West Siloam Springs...            Oaks...
Natural Falls State Park...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
